    ],
    "definition": "The Online Safety Act 2023 places a duty of care on providers of user-to-user services and search engines. Services must take proactive steps to protect users from illegal content and, for larger platforms, from legal but harmful content. Age appropriateness and effective age verification are core requirements for services accessible to children.",
    "checksAndBalances": "Age Verification (AV) gateway with configurable intensity (Soft → Systemic). Content moderation tooling with automated flagging. Transparency reports. Nominated Senior Manager accountability. Ofcom-compliant Terms of Service. Risk assessments refreshed annually.",
    "risksAndConsequences": "Non-compliance may result in Ofcom enforcement notices, fines up to £18M or 10% of global turnover, and in severe cases, service disruption orders. Criminal liability may attach to nominated Senior Managers. Reputational damage from public enforcement action is significant.",
    "createdAt": "2026-04-13T10:18:16.862Z",
    "implementationGuide": [
      {
        "id": "osa-step-1",
        "order": 1,
        "title": "Risk Assessment",
        "description": "Conduct and document a Children's Risk Assessment",
        "guidance": "Ofcom requires all in-scope services to complete a Children's Risk Assessment before implementing age verification. This must identify how the service could be accessed by children and what harms they may encounter.",
        "instructions": "## Children's Risk Assessment\n\n### What you need to do\n1. Identify all user journeys where children could access content\n2. Classify content types present on the platform (UGC, curated, AI-generated)\n3. Assess likelihood of children accessing each content category\n4. Document mitigations for each identified risk\n5. Record the assessment with date and responsible Senior Manager signature\n\n### Evidence Required\n- Completed risk assessment document (PDF)\n- Sign-off from nominated Senior Manager\n\n### Ofcom Guidance\nSee: [Ofcom Children's Risk Assessment Guidance](https://www.ofcom.org.uk/online-safety/information-for-industry/guidance-for-services)",
        "evidenceRequired": true,
        "automatable": false,
        "estimatedMinutes": 60,
        "status": "active",
        "draftable": true
      },
      {
        "id": "osa-step-2",
        "order": 2,
        "title": "Age Verification Strategy",
        "description": "Select and document your AV approach",
        "guidance": "Choose the AV intensity appropriate to your risk assessment. Soft = self-declaration, Hard = DOB validation with session gate. Document your rationale.",
        "instructions": "## Age Verification Strategy Selection\n\n### Intensity Options\n| Level | Method | Dial Position |\n|:--|:--|:--|\n| **Soft** | Self-declaration checkbox | Soft |\n| **Standard** | Date of birth picker + session cookie | Hard |\n| **Full ID** | Third-party ID verification (Yoti, ACCS) | Systemic |\n\n### Recommended Approach\nFor most SaaS platforms: **Standard (Hard)** — DOB picker with JS validation.\n\n### Steps\n1. Use the Intensity Dial on the policy card to select your approach\n2. Document your rationale referencing your risk assessment\n3. Upload evidence of the strategy decision",
        "evidenceRequired": true,
        "automatable": false,
        "estimatedMinutes": 30,
        "dependsOn": [
          "osa-step-1"
        ],
        "status": "locked"
      },
      {
        "id": "osa-step-3",
        "order": 3,
        "title": "Implement AV Gateway",
        "description": "Deploy the AV component to user-facing apps",
        "guidance": "The AV gateway must gate access before any user-generated or AI-generated content is displayed.",
        "instructions": "## Implementing the AV Gateway\n\n### What to Build\nA client-side component that:\n1. Checks for a valid age-verification session cookie\n2. If absent, shows a DOB picker modal\n3. Validates age ≥ 18\n4. Sets a session cookie on success\n5. Redirects to the content only after verification\n\n### Config in PromptResources\nThe Active Controller will set this config flag when you activate the Hard dial:\n```\nsystem_config/protection: { avEnabled: true, avStrictness: \"standard\" }\n```\n\n### Verifying\nUse the \"Run Check\" button to probe PromptResources automatically.",
        "evidenceRequired": true,
        "automatable": true,
        "automatedProbeId": "probe-av-gateway",
        "estimatedMinutes": 120,
        "dependsOn": [
          "osa-step-2"
        ],
        "status": "locked"
