    ],
    "definition": "Technical security hardening requirements for all applications in the Prompt Suite. Covers HTTPS enforcement, HTTP security headers, Firestore security rules, API key management, and dependency vulnerability management. Aligned with NCSC Cyber Essentials framework.",
    "checksAndBalances": "HTTPS enforced across all apps. Security headers (HSTS, CSP, X-Frame-Options, etc.) configured. Firestore security rules deny unauthenticated write access. API secrets stored encrypted in centralised secret store. Dependency scanning in CI pipeline.",
    "risksAndConsequences": "Security breaches leading to data exposure trigger DPA breach notification obligations (72h to ICO). Customer trust damage. Potential liability for consequential losses. Denial of service if vulnerabilities are exploited.",
    "implementationGuide": [
      {
        "id": "sec-step-1",
        "order": 1,
        "title": "HTTPS Enforcement",
        "description": "Verify all apps are served over HTTPS only",
        "guidance": "No HTTP endpoints should be accessible. Redirect all HTTP to HTTPS.",
        "instructions": "## HTTPS Enforcement\n\n### Verification Steps\n1. Check Firebase Hosting / Cloud Run config enforces HTTPS\n2. Verify next.config.js or headers config includes HSTS\n3. Test with: `curl -I http://your-app.web.app` — should redirect 301\n\n### HSTS Header\nAdd to Next.js config:\n```js\nheaders: [{ key: 'Strict-Transport-Security', value: 'max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains' }]\n```",
        "evidenceRequired": false,
        "automatable": true,
        "automatedProbeId": "probe-security-headers",
        "estimatedMinutes": 30,
        "status": "active"
      },
      {
        "id": "sec-step-2",
        "order": 2,
        "title": "Security Headers",
        "description": "Configure HTTP security response headers",
        "guidance": "Add CSP, X-Frame-Options, X-Content-Type-Options, Referrer-Policy to all app responses.",
        "instructions": "## Security Headers Configuration\n\n### Required Headers\n| Header | Value | Purpose |\n|:--|:--|:--|\n| Strict-Transport-Security | max-age=63072000 | Force HTTPS |\n| X-Frame-Options | DENY | Prevent clickjacking |\n| X-Content-Type-Options | nosniff | Prevent MIME sniffing |\n| Referrer-Policy | strict-origin-when-cross-origin | Limit referrer leakage |\n| Content-Security-Policy | default-src 'self' | Prevent XSS |\n\n### Next.js Implementation\nAdd to `next.config.js` headers() function.\n\n### Active Controller Fix\nClick \"Active Fix\" to push security header config to all apps' system_config/security in Firestore.",
        "evidenceRequired": false,
        "automatable": true,
        "automatedProbeId": "probe-security-headers",
        "estimatedMinutes": 45,
        "dependsOn": [
